-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-ARM Holdings, Bankia 
-- 
-- Wed Oct 22, 2014 02:10AM EDT
-- None



Oct 22 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including ARM Holdings and Bankia, on Wednesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * ARM Holdings Plc <ARM.L>: UBS raises to buy from neutral  * Bankia SA <BKIA.MC>: Citigroup cuts to neutral from buy * Evraz Plc <EVRE.L>: Jefferies cuts to underperform Following is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Wednesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.   * ARM Holdings Plc <ARM.L>: UBS raises to buy from neutral  * ARM Holdings Plc <ARM.L>: UBS raises price target to 980p from 970p * Banco BPI <BBPI.LS>: Citigroup cuts target to 1.55 euros from 1.60 euros; rating hold * Banco De Sabadell SA <SABE.MC>: Citigroup raises target to 1.95 euros; rating sell   * Banco SanTANDER SA <SAN.MC>: Citigroup cuts target to 7.30 euros from 7.60 euros; neutrAL  * Bankia SA <BKIA.MC>: Citigroup cuts to neutral from buy * Bankia SA <BKIA.MC>: Citigroup cuts price target to 1.35 euros from 1.80 euros  * Caixabank SA <CABK.MC>: Citigroup cuts target to 5.20 euros from 5.30 euros; rating buy   * Countrywide Plc< CWD.L>: Panmure cuts price target to 565p from 700p; rating buy  * Evraz Plc <EVRE.L>: Jefferies cuts to underperform